title: Westbound I-90 blocked by fiery semi crash near Vantage
text:
Westbound Interstate 90 was closed after a semi-truck crashed and caught fire.
The Washington State Patrol tweeted a photo of the crash about 7:15 a.m. Monday.
Though the semi burned, no one was hurt.
The crash is near milepost 127.
The left lane reopened at about 9 a.m.
I90 WB mp127 is blocked due to a semi collision with fire. Non injury. pic.twitter.com/yNPRZCQTqM
